children.subject: Just a heads up I doubt as many people will drop the class this semester..

history.content:
In the past, people dropped because the course demanded a lot of students' times (with Prof. Sahai Fall 2017/Spring 2018 and Profs. Recht/Yu/Hardt this sem) but given that Prof. Shewchuk said the course would be 'an average CS upperdiv' in workload that would be pretty unlikely for next sem. Also keep in mind a lot of people have probably been waiting to take it until now, or heard all the hype from 3 sems ago and have just now gotten around to completing all the prerequisite material that was demanded by previous profs.

tldr; highly doubt 500 people are going to drop a regular class

children.subject: Hi, Im waitlist 390 as well. Is there no chance of getting in even though the class will be expanded? I was thinking if you're position ~400 you have a good chance of getting in.

history.content:
The 189 waitlist currently has about 500 students. I've heard that the class might be expanded and I'm unsure about whether I should stay on the waitlist or enroll in an alternate class while I still have the time. Berkeleytime shows that enough people drop the class eventually for the enrollment to reach 90%. Is it safe to assume that the same would happen this Spring or should I look at other classes? 

(I'm about 400th on the waitlist)
